<HEADLINE> More Than 150,000 PLA Soldiers Fighting Yangtze Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) today air-dropped 3,000 officers and soldiers
into Wuhan to fight the upcoming sixth flood crest.
</P>
<P>
The officers and men, who came from central China's Henan
Province, were air-dropped by 14 airplanes at noon today.
</P>
<P>
So far, the number of PLA soldiers and armed police fighting
floods on the Yangtze River dikes have increased to 150,000, said
a PLA commander directing the anti-flood battle on the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
During the past three days, the military area commands of
Guangzhou and Jinan have sent emergency troops to reinforce
the Yangtze dikes as many sections are in danger of breaches as a
result of swollen water and flood-weakened dikes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
