<HEADLINE> Highway, Railway Traffic Suspended in Daqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAQING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Railway traffic between Ranghu
and Tongliao near China's largest oil field of Daqing in northeast
China's Heilongjiang Province was suspended today because of
flood damage on a 5-kilometer section.
</P>
<P>
At present, the rails are 1.5 meters beneath the floodwater,
and the water is reportedly rising.
</P>
<P>
The highway between Xinzhan and Zhaoyuan in the same region has
also been inundated by floodwater from the Nenjiang River.
</P>
<P>
A rush repair team of 400 people is working on the damaged
railway and highway sections.  
</P>
</TEXT>
