<HEADLINE> 200 Injured in Gallery Collapse in Calcutta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 200 people were
injured, some of them critically, when an overcrowded gallery at a
sports ground in Calcutta, the largest city in eastern India,
collapsed on Wednesday, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The gallery collapsed barely 20 minutes into a football match
at the Mohammedan Sports Ground. Nearly 10,000 spectators were
watching the Calcutta supper division league tie between
Mohammedan Sporting Club and Peerless, PTI said.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a police officer, PTI said that irate fans set the
gallery and the press box on fire, reducing them to ashes, and
ransacked the club tent nearby.
</P>
<P>
Rapid Action Force personnel rushed to the spot and made a
lathi charge to bring the situation under control as the players
were escorted to safety, said PTI.
</P>
<P>
Police and the fire brigade personnel rushed the injured to
nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The state government of West Bengal has ordered a high-level
inquiry into the incident, said PTI. 
</P>
</TEXT>
