<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Steps to Curb Worsening Security Situation in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Islamic Sharia courts and
businessmen are enlarging their campaign against the widespread
banditry in Mogadishu and its surrounding areas to curb the
deteriorating security situation in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The killings and banditry in the capital continue with a
number of people being killed at random in the streets of
Mogadishu every day since two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Three people were killed and six others wounded Monday at k-7
check-point controlled by faction leader Osman Ali Atto.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, a group of gunmen manning the
check-point opened fire on a land cruiser transporting passengers
from Ballidogle Airport.
</P>
<P>
A man known as Abdi Hassan who had just arrived from Canada to
see his family died on the spot. The vehicle was seized by the
gunmen.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday afternoon, a newspaper man identified as Ali Fiyus
was shot dead around the main charcoal selling area of Bakara
market in south Mogadishu controlled by Hussein Mohamed Aidid.
</P>
<P>
At least 13 bandits and looters have been rounded up around
the main Bakara market by the security force established by
businessmen.
</P>
<P>
The sweep operation by the market's security force followed a
clear warning by the business committee that all bandits caught
during the operation will be dealt with severely while their
families will not be given any compensation if the bandits were
killed.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement released by the business community
committee Tuesday, all bandits caught red-handed will be turned
over to the Islamic courts for trial according to the Sharia
laws.
</P>
<P>
The banditry and counter banditry activities are going on as
three Islamic courts in Mogadishu have also declared the
unification of their forces for propagating the Islamic Sharia
laws throughout Mogadishu and its surrounding areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
