<HEADLINE> Security Council Urges Tajik Parties to Fully </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council on Wednesday urged parties in Tajikistan to
increase their efforts to fully implement the peace agreement
reached between them.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after the Council reviewed U.N.
Secretary-General's latest report on the situation in the country,
the Current Council President Danilo Turk said through some
progress had been achieved in the process of Tajikistan's national
reconciliation, the situation there remained unstable.
</P>
<P>
The members of the Council called upon the parties concerned to
make good use of the continuing international backing for the
peace process of the country and urged them to refrain form any
actions that were contrary to the peace agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Council welcomed U.N. Secretary-General's intention to take
additional steps to ensure the safety of U.N. mission there and
reiterated that the main responsibility for the security of U.N.
mission lies within the Tajik parties.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council also urged the Government of Tajikistan
and the United Tajik Opposition to take steps to accelerate the
investigation of the murder of four members of U.N. mission on
July 20 and bring those responsible for the murder to justice as
soon as possible. 
</P>
