<HEADLINE> Israel Criticizes PNA for Barring Entry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Israel sharply criticized the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) on Wednesday for its barring
the entry into a Jewish holy site in the West Bank city of
Nablus.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, Israeli Prime Minister's Office
said that the PNA's refusal to allow Jews to pray at the Jewish
patriarch Joseph's Tomb in Nablus was a violation of the Oslo
accords.
</P>
<P>
Under the Oslo accords, both Israel and the Palestinians will
protect the religious rights of Jews, Christians and Muslims. This
includes protection of holy sites, ensuring free access to the
sites and freedom of worship and religious practice.
</P>
<P>
The statement came after the Palestinian police continued to
blockade the tomb on Wednesday and only allowed food and
beverages to be taken into the site, where 28 Jewish religious
students have remained since last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian officials decided to close the site last week,
which is inside the Nablus city that was under the PNA control,
after the Jewish students refused to leave the tomb at night.
</P>
<P>
During the Israeli-Palestinian bloodshed in September 1996 that
was sparked by Israel's opening an underground tunnel in East
Jerusalem, the site of Joseph's Tomb witnessed one of the
bloodiest clashes between Israeli troops and Palestinian police
and protesters, during which six Israeli soldiers were killed.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian side feared that the students will turn the
tomb into a permanent settlement if they are allowed to remain in
the site 24 hours a day.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an Israeli senior defense source was quoted by
Israel Radio as saying that the issue of staying overnight in
the tomb is not detailed in any agreement between Israel and the
PNA.
</P>
<P>
He said the Israeli discussions with the PNA were continuing
and a peaceful solution could be found shortly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980820.0025 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-19 17:36 </DATE_TIME>
