that included senior officials from the ministries of health,
industry and social policy.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav minister will hold further talks with other Iraqi
officials to discuss the possibility of signing trade deals under
the Iraq-U.N. oil-for-food program.
</P>
<P>
Under the fourth phase of the oil-for-food deal, which came
into force on June 3, Iraq is allowed to export 5.2 billion
U.S. dollars worth of oil in six months to buy food, medicine and
other humanitarian supplies for its suffering people. 
</P>
