<HEADLINE> Turkey's Population Reaches 62 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's population has grown to
62.86 million from 61.6 million in 1995, according to results of
the latest census announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, State Minister Mehmet
Batalli said the census, conducted last November, shows that 40.88
million people, or 65 percent of the total population, live in
cities.
</P>
<P>
The three biggest cities are Istanbul, the capital Ankara and
the Aegean city Izmir, with respective population of 9.05 million,
3.63 million and 3.06 million, according to Batalli.
</P>
<P>
The census also shows that unlike in the cities and towns, the
growth rate in rural areas have actually decreased. 
</P>
