<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Financing for Reorganization of Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank Wednesday announced the approval of a 22.5 million
U.S. dollar soft loan to Haiti to support the first stage of a
reorganization of the national health system.
</P>
<P>
The project will provide technical assistance, training and
material inputs to implement a local network model of health
services delivery in four geographic areas and establish a funding
channel for those services.
</P>
<P>
The model, referred to as Communal Health Unit, will benefit
around two million Haitians and includes the provision of a
cost-effective package of health services under contracts or
performance agreements, health promotion and community
participation activities. The initiative will also support
strengthening of the central and departmental directorates of the
health sector.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the first stage of the project is some 25
million dollars. Local counterpart funding for this phase totals
about 2.5 million dollars. 
