<HEADLINE> Germany Sees More Poor People in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The number of people who had to get
social welfare aid increased to 2.92 million in Germany by the end
of 1997, up 7.1 percent from a year ago, the German Federal
Statistics Office said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The most dramatic increase was registered in the poorer eastern
Germany, where the total number of social welfare recipients grew
by 23.9 percent in 1997 compared with an increase of only 4.9
percent in the western half of the country, the latest figures
released by the Wiesbaden-based statistics office showed.
</P>
<P>
German authorities blamed the latest increase in the number of
social welfare recipients mainly to high unemployment in the
country which rose to about 4.5 million by the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Among those poor people, 56 percent were women and 44 percent
men, the statistics office said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
