<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Close Off Day's Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 19 (Xinhua) -- European stock markets lost most
of the day's gains as they closed Wednesday, in response to a
lackluster performance on Wall Street, despite a strong showing
from Asian equities and an improvement in the yen.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 in London enjoyed a late burst of activity to
finish with modest gains, with the index closing 46.1 higher at
5694.3, on moderate volume of 747 million shares.
</P>
<P>
A positive performance on most Asian markets and Wall Street's
strong gains Tuesday made a bullish mood early on, with the FTSE
100 recording a session high of 5,712.8 in late morning.
</P>
<P>
But as U.S. stocks were unable to build on Tuesday's gains,
London was lost in direction in afternoon trade.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said there was still some bearish sentiment about as
Asian concerns continued to figure, despite recent gains in those
markets. Volatility was predicted to continue for some time.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the German Dax slumped near its close, giving up
much of an early 2 percent advance. This underscored analysts'
concerns that the temporary show of strength did not hail a return
of a bull market.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 30-share, blue-chip Dax index stood at
5,596.41, up 27.53 points or 0.49 percent, below the key 5,600
level and well off its early high of 56,72.07.
</P>
<P>
In electronic trading, which continues for a half hour after
the floor session, the Xetra DAX was virtually unchanged, ending
at 5,601.93, down about one quarter of one point.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, share prices closed off the day's highs, too, falling
back from its early levels late in the session as Wall Street
pared early gains.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 index closed 2.47 points higher at 4,125.72, below
the day's high of 4,159.70. August CAC-40 futures closed 26 points
higher at 4,146. 
</P>
