deputy mayor of Yssingeaux, the city that hosted the Iranian
national football team during the World Cup earlier this year,
and Jean-Michel Boucheron, president of the group of France-Iran
Friendship in the National Assembly, will accompany Vedrine during
 the visit.
</P>
<P>
Vedrine's visit to Iran will be the first by a French foreign
minister since Roland Dumas in 1991.
</P>
<P>
French Minister of Equipment Bernard Pons visited Teheran in
1996. 
