<HEADLINE> Pledges Made to Fight Against Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINGZHOU, August 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,000 soldiers and
civilians today gathered at a major embankment on the Yangtze
River to pledge mass effort to fight against the raging floods.
</P>
<P>
The gathering, organized by the Hubei provincial government and
the headquarters of the flood-control military forces on the
forefront, was designed to spread the important instructions of
President Jiang Zemin on flood control and to mobilize people to
unite to win the anti-flood battle.
</P>
<P>
Among the participants at the gathering were Tao Bojun,
Commander of the Guangzhou Military Area Command; Shi Yuxiao,
Political Commissar of the Guangzhou Military Area Command; Jia
Zhijie, Secretary of the Hubei Provincial Committee of the
Communist Party of China; and Jiang Zhuping, governor of Hubei.
</P>
<P>
The worst-ever flooding has hit the Yangtze River Valley since
this summer, resulting in a great loss of lives and property.
</P>
<P>
Because of the concerted effort of hundreds of thousands of
soldiers and civilians, the major dikes on the Yangtze River have
survived the ravages of five flood crests this year, with a sixth
moving downstream.
</P>
<P>
"Though great victories have been scored, the high water level
is expected to stay for a fairly long period of time and the
flood-control task is still gravely arduous," Jia Zhijie said at
the gathering.
</P>
<P>
"We must persist, persist and persist again to ensure the
safety of the major embankments of the Yangtze River," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tao Bojun urged the military forces to build up a great wall of
iron and steel to counter the floods.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that leading officials of the flooded areas have
been role models in flood-control.
</P>
<P>
In Hubei, both Jia Zhijie and Jiang Zhuping have for weeks
fought on the forefront.
</P>
<P>
In Hunan Province, Chu Bo, Deputy Secretary of the
Provincial Party Committee, has been commanding the anti-flood
effort for nearly one month.
</P>
<P>
Luo Diansu, publicity chief of Yueyang City, Hunan Province,
fell faint on an embankment. Luo's heart problem was attributed to
working more than 40 days on the embankment.
</P>
<P>
In east China's Jiangxi Province, Secretary of Provincial Party
Committee Shu Huiguo, Governor Shu Shengyou and many other
grassroots officials have been among the first to appear whenever
the flooding situation was most critical. 
</P>
</TEXT>
