his personal season best, while his compatriot Luciano di Pardo
won the second heat featuring most of the stars in 8:26.52.
</P>
<P>
The European junior champion Georg Weidlinger tripped over one
of the obstacles and hit his head on the barrier between the
track and the field. Weidlinger was taken to hospital immediately.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 leader Venelina Veneva of Bulgaria, qualified toge
ther with Romanian Monica Dinescu, who with four jumps over 2
meter is the years most consistent jumper.
</P>
<P>
In the men's decathlon Finland's Eduard Hamalainen was on
course for gold after six events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
