<HEADLINE> Sales of Duty Free Shop of Dubai Airport Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Sales of the duty free shop of
the Dubai airport, one of the best duty free shops in the world,
have risen to 195 million U.S. dollars in 1997 as compared to 184
million dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released Thursday by the Civil Aviation Department
in Dubai said that sales of the Dubai airport duty free shop
represented 33 per cent of the total duty free shop sales of the
world over during 1996 which stood at 558 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Dubai airport duty free shop succeeded last year in winning
more than 65 world prizes.
</P>
<P>
The last were two international prizes earned during the first
six months of the current year, namely, the "best airport duty
free shop in the world", and the "best duty free shop in the
world". 
</P>
