<HEADLINE> Xi'an High-Tech Zone Leads Northwest China in Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Xi'an High-Tech Industrial
Development Zone of Shaanxi Province has led northwest China in
economic development with more than 400 kinds of high-tech
products selling well on domestic and overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
Founded in March of 1991, the Xi'an site is one of China's 52
state-level high-tech industrial development zones.
</P>
<P>
It is now home to 548 new and high-tech industrial businesses
and has established an industrial network consisting of six major
industries, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Seventy of the industrial enterprises reported more than 10
million yuan of annual earnings each from technological transfers,
industrial production and trade.
</P>
<P>
The development zone produced 10 billion yuan in total earnings
from technological transfers, industrial production and trade and
generated an industrial output value of 6.3 billion yuan in 1997, a
rise of 30 percent and 31 percent on 1996. 
