<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dell Computer Begins Direct Sales in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Dell Computer Corp., the world's
leading direct marketer of computer systems, began direct sales
today in China. The fastest growing computer firm now has found a
home in the world's fastest growing computer market.
</P>
<P>
Direct computer sales is a two-layer business operation based
on a direct relationship between the manufacturer and the customer
without intermediaries such as distributors and resellers.
</P>
<P>
Morton Topfer, vice chairman of Dell Computer, said in an
exclusive interview here today with Xinhua that the company's
direct sales will have nine locations in such major Chinese cities
as Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
Customers can make purchases and request technical support via
toll-free 24-hour hotlines or by shopping at a virtual "store" on
the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Individual and corporate customers can receive Dell's
"built-to-order" service that is uniform around the world,
according to Topfer, and can choose from extensive configuration
choices.
</P>
<P>
Products will be delivered within seven working days after the
order is placed, he said, and technicians will provide next-day,
on-site installation and other support services.
</P>
<P>
Industry analysts say the direct computer business will
generate strong incentives in China's fledgling computer market,
since cheaper computers with the latest software are more
attractive to potential buyers who have limited financial
resources.
</P>
<P>
In 14 years of business, Dell has become the second largest
computer systems company in the world after Compaq Computer
Corp.
</P>
<P>
Topfer attributed this success to the integration of research
and development, production, sales and after-sales service that
makes Dell more flexible to market changes and ready for
state-of-the-art technologies.
</P>
<P>
Jim King, sales and marketing vice president of Dell Computer
(China) Co., Ltd., said the Dell products available directly to
Chinese customers range from desktop and notebook personal
computer to servers. The Dell China Customer Center located in
Xiamen operates the manufacturing, sales and telephone services.
</P>
<P>
According to International Data Company's forecast at the end
of the first quarter, China's personal computer market is expected
to more than triple in size by 2002 to 10.6 million units, making
China the largest in the Asia Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The current annual sales of Dell is 15.2 billion U.S. dollars,
and the online Dell Store sells 6 million dollars of products and
services every day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
