<HEADLINE> Graphite Deposit Discovered in Hebei Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese geologists have
discovered a high-grade graphite deposit in Longhua County, Hebei
Province, with a potential reserve of 15 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The large-scale graphite deposit is six kilometers long and one
kilometer wide on the border between the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region and Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Graphite, a metalloid material, is widely used in
metallurgical, casting, petroleum, atomic energy and national
defense industries.
</P>
<P>
Graphite deposits previously were found only in the provinces
of Shandong, Heilongjiang and Hunan, and the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region.  
</P>
