<HEADLINE> Former East German Officials Fined in Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, August 20 (Xinhua) - Three former East German sports
officials were found guilty on doping charges and fined by a
Berlin court on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Doctors Ulrich Suender and Dorit Roesler and trainer Peter
Mattonet, accused of damaging the health of 17 swimmers between
1979 and 1989 by administering steroids through pills or
injections, were fined up to 27,000 marks.
</P>
<P>
Suender, 58, was fined 27,000 marks while the 50-year-old
Roesler and the 48-year-old Mattonet were ordered to pay 7,200
and 7,000 marks ($3,906).
</P>
<P>
The three were among five officials who worked for the
swimming section of the former TSC Berlin club and whose trial
opened on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The other two, coaches Berndt Christochowitz, 40, and Klaus
Klemenz, 55, were fined 7,500 marks and 3,000 marks earlier on
Thursday and had the case against them dropped. 
</P>
