<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Revenue Rise 6.6 Pct in First 5 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The revenue earned by the Sri
Lankan government during the first five months of this year
registered a 6.6 percent increase over the same period last year,
according to the latest statistics of the Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
A Central Bank spokesman said Thursday that 63.64 million U.S.
dollars were collected by the state from January to May this year
more than last year's same period total of 968.18 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said a total of 2.854 billion U.S. dollars are expected to
be earned as the government revenue this year.
</P>
<P>
