<HEADLINE> Benefit Performance for Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Preparations for a large
benefit performance for China's flood victims are going smoothly,
and the performance will be held at 8 p.m.on tomorrow evening as
scheduled, the Ministry of Civil Affairs said today.
</P>
<P>
The show, co-organized by the ministries of Culture and Civil
Affairs, will include performances by nearly 1,000 Chinese
singers, dancers and movie stars, including artists from Hong
Kong, Taiwan and some foreign countries. This major event will be
staged in the prestigious Great Hall of the People in downtown
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
China Central Television, which last Sunday hosted an evening
show which raised over 600 million RMB yuan (about 75 million
U.S. dollars) in donations for the flood-stricken areas, will
offer a live broadcast of the benefit performance.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Civil Affairs has opened four donation hotlines
for the performance. Those numbers are: (8610) 66011500, 66011800,
66053100 and 66053700.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry also has pledged that every penny of the funds
raised will be used for the country's flood victims, whose total
number has exceeded 240 million.
</P>
<P>
According to the local news media, the Municipal Government of
Beijing is also hosting a benefit performance this evening.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, domestic and foreign donations sent to the Ministry
of Civil Affairs and its sub-departments across the country have
to date totalled over 1.06 billion RMB yuan (about 130 million U.S.
dollars), said a Ministry official today.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry has allocated relief materials worth some 131
million yuan to the flooded areas, the official added.
</P>
