<HEADLINE> U.S. to Impose Sanction on Angola's UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton has
ordered to freeze all the assets and other interests of the
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The Angolan News Agency Thursday quoted a Washington source as
saying that the holidaying Clinton issued the order Wednesday in
Massachusetts, banning any sale of transport tools and mining
equipment to the UNITA-controlled area.
</P>
<P>
The sanction also bans import of diamond from the southern
African country without the permission of the Angolan government.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to leaders of both houses of the Congress, Clinton
said that his move is to implement the United Nations' No.1173
resolution on sanctioning UNITA.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the sanction, passed in June this year, is to cut
off UNITA's economic supply.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said that UNITA's policy and action are posing a
continued threat to the peace process in Angola and run against
U.S. foreign policy. 
</P>
