<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Thursday although profit
taking in the afternoon halted recent rapid rise.
</P>
<P>
The buying interest in the morning was not sustained as players
started selling in the afternoon on profit-taking. Dealers said
they were pessimistic on short term outlook concerning the market.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was up
7.57 points to 351.04, the all-share Emas Index added 1.77 points
to 89.99, the Industrial Index gained 3.84 points to 705.77 and
the Second Board Index rose 2.55 points to 81.59.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers 491 to 174 while 131 counters were
unchanged, 126 untraded and 36 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 391.669 million shares valued
at 548.277 million ringgit (131.797 million U.S. dollars) from
312.522 million shares valued at 412.421 million ringgit (99.139
million U.S. dollars) traded Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover increased to 370.411 million shares
valued at 525.726 million ringgit (126.376 million U.S. dollars)
from Wednesday's 303.582 million shares worth 404.538 million
ringgit (97.244 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover rose to 21.258 million shares worth
22.551 million ringgit (5.42 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 8.940 million shares valued at 7.883 million ringgit
(1.894 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market deals rose to 3.092 million shares valued at 2.988
million ringgit (0.718 million U.S. dollars) from 859,500 shares
valued at 2.375 million ringgit (0.57 million U.S. dollars)
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
