<HEADLINE> 20 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northeast Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 Tamil rebels were
killed and a large number of others wounded in separate
confrontations with government troops in northern and eastern Sri
Lanka Wednesday, the military spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said the troops ambushed and killed 10 Tamil rebels
northeast of Kattaparichchan in eastern Trincomalee district
Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
However, two soldiers also died and four others were injured in
the incident.
</P>
<P>
The same day, troops conducted a limited operation at
Manaikkadu in Batticaloa district. Rebels initially withdrew with
the arrival of troops but fired mortars at the advancing troops in
the evening. the troops retaliated with mortars and artillery
fire.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said eight rebels were confirmed killed and a
large number injured while three soldiers were also killed and
eight others wounded in the operation.
</P>
<P>
The rebels launched an attack on the air force defenses south
of Mankulam town Wednesday, he said, adding that air force troops
retaliated effectively causing casualties among the rebels.
</P>
<P>
On a subsequent search in the area, the troops recovered two
rebel dead bodies with a large stock of weapons.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the country. 
</P>
