<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Aids Small, Medium-sized Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is launching a wide
spectrum of promotions to help enhance the competitiveness of
small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), which account for 98
percent of the total number of local firms.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC) Thursday opened
the Market Day Exhibition "SMEs: Competing in a Changing World",
an event to familiarize entrepreneurs with the council's 300 trade
promotion activities worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Held concurrently with the two-day exhibition are 16 seminars,
where government officials, market experts and business
professionals discuss opportunities and challenges faced by the
SMEs.
</P>
<P>
