<HEADLINE> Western Jilin Province Free of Infectious Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAICHENG, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Epidemic control teams have
successfully prevented outbreak of infectious diseases in flooded
areas around the city of Baicheng in western Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
The first shipment of medical supplies arrived in the
northeast China city on July 31, and a large task force of
medical personnel are working in provincial hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The city's epidemic control station requires outlying branches
to immediately report emergency cases and submit normal status
reports every three days.
</P>
<P>
Medical teams and the local Red Cross Society have offered
round-the-clock services and distributed medical products valued
at some 7,000 yuan (843 US dollars) to people living in
flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that disinfectants and medical supplies valued
at 670,000 yuan (80,700 US dollars) have been distributed in
flooded areas.
</P>
<P>
The healthcare department has called for the economic use of
medical supplies to prevent future shortages.  
