<HEADLINE> Israel Tightens Hold on Jerusalem, Says PLC Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Legislative Council
speaker warned Thursday that Israel is implementing a more
aggressive policy on Jerusalem, the holy city the Palestinians
want as their future capital.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Qureia (Abu Ala) raised the alarm in an interview with
Egypt's Voice of Arabs radio.
</P>
<P>
But for the Arabs in general and the Palestinians in
particular, "without Jerusalem there will be no peace," he said.
