<P>
Criticizing the policy of Tel Aviv as procrastination, Qureia
said Israel is determined to bring about radical changes to the
signed peace agreements between the Palestinians and Israelis
since 1993.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu has declined an invitation to a meeting in Norway next
week marking the fifth anniversary of the Oslo peace accords,
citing his busy engagement at home.
</P>
<P>
In a move that has sparked strong Arab condemnations, the
Israeli cabinet passed a decision on June 21 on expanding the
municipal borders of Jerusalem to cover surrounding settlements
and vast areas of the West Bank territories.
</P>
<P>
Israel captured East Jerusalem in 1967 and later annexed it, a
move that has failed to win international recognition. The
Palestinians want East Jerusalem as the capital of their future
state.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli peace talks were deadlocked in March
last year over Israel's settlement building in East Jerusalem and
long-delayed troop withdrawal from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The recent talks between the two sides failed to achieve any
progress because Israel has rejected a U.S. initiative on further
redeployment, which has been accepted by the Palestinians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
