Laurent Kabila of backing the rebel invasion in his country. But
the two countries denied the charge.
</P>
<P>
On their arrival in Cape Town, Nzo and Modise briefed Mbeki.
The talks reportedly continued until midnight.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday morning the two ministers briefed Mandela and
Mbeki ahead of Mandela's scheduled meeting with Nujoma.
</P>
<P>
Namibia reportedly supports Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe's call for military intervention to help Kabila quell the
uprisings by Banyamulenge soldiers who helped Kabila overthrow
late president Mobutu Sese Seko in May 1997.
</P>
<P>
Rebels in the country reportedly announced Wednesday that they
were ready to negotiate with Kabila. 
