without depending on foreign financial assistance."
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian government which already announced a number of
measures to extricate itself from a difficult economic position
precipitated by attacks on regional currencies in July last year
has been prompted to consider even more drastic measures as the
country's economy is still reeling from the downturn.
</P>
<P>
Urging the people to be prepared for these measures, Mahathir
said, "It may be shocking to the foreigners but they are aimed at
putting the economy back on the right track."
</P>
<P>
"I have also forewarned the people that the measures could be
shocking, but whether they are shocking or not, I hope all parties
will support them," Mahathir said without spelling out what the
measures would be. 
