<HEADLINE> Aid For China's Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- China's State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters sent more materials to flood-ravaged
areas along the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River and
the Nen and Songhua rivers in the Northeast today.
</P>
<P>
Most of the materials went to Hunan, Hubei, Heilongjiang, and
Jilin provinces, which are at a crucial stage in their battle with
the sixth flood crest on the Yangtze and the third on the Songhua.
</P>
<P>
By August 19, the headquarters had sent 200 million yuan worth
of goods to the areas.
</P>
<P>
An embankment along the Yangtze in Hubei Province was hit by
44.6-meter-deep flood waters.
</P>
<P>
Many medical workers are working to prevent an outbreak of
epidemic diseases.
</P>
<P>
In neighboring Hunan Province, people have been donating money
and goods to help flood-stricken residents. In half a month, the
Hunan Office for Disaster Relief and Donations received 26 million
yuan in cash and 20 million yuan worth of goods.
</P>
<P>
In Anhui Province in the East, 1.2 million soldiers and
civilians have dealt with danger spots at 12,000 places along a
765-km embankment along the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
In Heilongjiang Province on the Songhua, 2,244 medical workers
have been giving medical aid and helping to prevent epidemic
diseases.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
