<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Inflation Expected to Rise to 32 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Reserve Bank of Zimbabwe
expects inflation to rise to 32 percent by next month owing
largely to inflationary pressures.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the inflation rise is said to be due to the
currency depreciation, fuel price adjustments and the effects of
this year's wage settlement.
</P>
<P>
But forecasts for the end of the year show that inflation will
decline to about 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate in July reached about 30 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
