<DOCNO> XIE19980820.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Harvest 1.68m Tons of Grain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Despite natural disasters in
some parts of the country, Mozambique is expected to harvest
about 1.686 million tons of grain this year, according to a
senior official.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Agostinho Rosario, Minister of Agriculture and Fishery
said here Wednesday that about 1.124 million tons of maize, the
staple food of Mozambicans, are to be harvested, about eight
percent higher than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Farmers are expected to get in about 318,000 tons of sorghum
and 191,000 tons of rice this year, both higher than those of
last year.
</P>
<P>
The grain harvest is attributed to the enlarged acreage after
war refugees and displaced people settled down for production.
</P>
<P>
Planting acreage this year grew to 3.72 million hectares from
3.63 hectares in the previous farming year.
</P>
<P>
Good weather is said to be another reason for the good
harvest, with only a few areas affected by drought or flood in
the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
