<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Eastern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 20 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake jolted Tokyo and its
vicinity in eastern Japan Thursday afternoon, the Meteorological
Agency said.
</P>
<P>
So far, there were no immediate reports of damage or
casualties, and no tsunami or tidal wave warnings were issued.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which occurred at 3:42 p.m. (local
time) with an measurement of 7.1 on the Richter scale, was 410
kilometers under the seabed near Torishima Island, south of Tokyo,
said the agency. 
</P>
