<HEADLINE> Chinese, German Joint Stamp Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- China and Germany jointly
released a set of special stamps on Thursday depicting two
cultural heritage sites, the Puning Temple in Chengde, an imperial
summer resort in China, and the Wurzburg Residence in Wurzburg,
Germany.
</P>
<P>
Issuing ceremonies were held simultaneously in the China's
capital, Beijing, and in Wurzburg.
</P>
<P>
The two stamps were designed by Xiao Yutian of China.
</P>
<P>
Puning Temple was built in 1755 with a combination of Han and
Tibetan architecture and has the country's largest wood-carved
Buddha. The Wurzburg Residence was built in 1719 in the style of
Paris' Versailles Palace. Both were imperial palaces and have been
put on UNESCO's world heritage list.  
</P>
</TEXT>
