Atlantic on Wednesday, the 39th held by the U.S. and the three
Latin American countries.
</P>
<P>
The joint fleet left Montevideo port this morning to carry out
simulated sea battles, landing and anti-submarine exercises. The
"United Operation" exercise, which will last for five days,
involves 2,000 troops, 12 warships, a nuclear submarine and naval
air forces from the four countries. (Uruguay-Military Exercise)
