</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The United Nations had recruited two oil
experts from Dutch Saybolt firm to help speed up Iraq's order,
receiving and installation of oil equipment, U.N. spokesman said
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council of the United Nations last May authorized
Iraq to sell 5.2 billion U.S. dollars worth of oil during the
subsequent six months, the so-called new U.N. oil-for-food
program. But Iraq complained that it did not have the capacity to
export such an amount of oil due to its shabby oil equipment. The
Council last June agreed to allow Iraq to import 300 million
U.S. dollars worth of spare parts to ungrade its dilapidated oil
industry. (UN-Iraq-Oil Equipment) 
</P>
