<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Sets Conditions on Suspended Stock Brokers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 20 (Xinhua) - The Philippine Stock Exchange
(PSE) Thursday bared the conditions set by the Securities and
Exchange Commission on member brokers who wish to suspend their
operations.
</P>
<P>
PSE president Jose Luis Yulo said there are two general
conditions that must be followed by member brokers prior to the
suspension of their operations.
</P>
<P>
One condition is that a member broker must make a request so
that he or she may be allowed to become a non-operating and
non-trading member of the stock exchange until the end of the
year, Yulo said.
</P>
<P>
The other condition is that as a non-operating member, he or
she shall be exempted from the submission of the financial
operation report and other reportorial requirements, he added.
</P>
<P>
The non-operating member can maintain a net capital of only two
million pesos (45,662 U.S. dollars). But when applying for renewal
of its license, the member must again have a minimum net capital
of five million pesos (114,155 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, Yulo said that only license nominees, officers and
staff of the non-operating member shall be allowed to continue
trading as agents of operating member brokers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
