<HEADLINE> Chinese Supreme Court Ruling on Chen Xitong's Appeal (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- China's Supreme People's Court
dismissed an appeal by Chen Xitong, the former secretary of the
Beijing Municipal Communist Party Committee today and upheld the
original judgement.
</P>
<P>
On July 31, 1998, the Beijing Municipal Higher People's Court
made a ruling of first instance on Chen's case, sentencing him to
13 years in prison for corruption and 4 years for dereliction of
duty. Chen will have to serve 16 years in prison and bribes he
accepted shall be confiscated and turned over to the State
Treasury.
</P>
<P>
Chen disagreed with the ruling and appealed to the Supreme
People's Court, which established a collegiate court to hear the
case in accordance with Article 187 of China's Criminal Procedure
Law.
</P>
<P>
The collegiate court heard Chen's statement and his lawyer's
defense and questioned him. It also reviewed the findings of first
instance of the Beijing Municipal Higher People's Court before
reaching a judgement.
</P>
<P>
The judicial committee of the Supreme People's Court said that
Chen, who was serving as a senior official, violated regulations,
accepted expensive gifts and illegally kept them. These it called
criminal acts of corruption. more
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980820.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Court Ruling on Chen Xitong's Appeal (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The committee said that Chen also conspired with Wang Baosen,
Beijing's former Vice-Mayor, to build luxury villas with public
funds for their own use, which resulted in a great loss of public
funds and losses to the state and people and were a criminal
dereliction of duty and must be punished.
</P>
<P>
It also rejected Chen's appeal and his lawyer's defense,
calling the Beijing Municipal Higher People's Court's ruling
correct in its understanding of the facts and its application of
the law and an appropriate publishment for Chen.
</P>
<P>
Article 197 of the Criminal Procedure Law stipulates that a
Supreme People's Court ruling is a judgement of final instance.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court's verdict in Chen's case was
effective immediately after it was announced to the public earlier
today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
