<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mercury, Sting Leave Liberty out of Playoffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Charlotte Sting and
Phoenix Mercury did Wednesday night what the New York Liberty
could not win to become the final two teams to qualify for the
WNBA playoffs.
</P>
<P>
Charlotte (18-12) put the pressure on the Liberty, who has to
go home after advancing to the title game a year ago, by blowing
out the Washington Mystics 105-69 earlier Wednesday night, but
the Sting still needed either New York or Phoenix to lose in
order to advance to the playoffs for the second straight season.
</P>
<P>
Charlotte did not have to wait long as New York (18-12) lost
to the Detriot Shock 82-68 while Phoenix (19-11) made sure it was
included in the postseason play by beating the Sacramento
Monarchs 71-62 to grab the third seed.
</P>
<P>
Cleveland Rockers (20-10), winner of the Eastern Conference
and the only newcomers to the playoffs, travel to Phoenix for
Game One of their semifinal series Saturday night. The conference
champions host Game Two and if necessary Game three.
</P>
<P>
All playoff series this season are best-of-three. The
inaugural WNBA playoffs last year were single-elimination affairs.
</P>
<P>
Charlotte posted the second-highest point total in WNBA
history in the regular-season finale for both teams here
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Andrea Stinson scored 25 points, Rhonda Mapp added 18 and
Tracy Reid has six of her seven points in a game-breaking first
half run for the Sting.
</P>
<P>
Charlotte became the third team to clinch a playoff berth when
the New York Liberty lost to the Detriot Shock. The Sting made
the playoffs last season and lost to eventual champion Houston
Comets in the first round.
</P>
<P>
Nikki McCray netted 20 points and Murriel Page added 15 for
the Mystics, who wound up their debut season with a 3-27 record
and a five-game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
The Comets have home-court advantage throughout the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
The semifinals begin Saturday with the WNBA Finals starting on
August 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
