<DOCNO> XIE19980820.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakh Finance Stable Despite Outside Disturbances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh financial market remains
stable despite some negative effects cast upon by the economic
crisis in southeast Asia and Russia, the Kazakh government and its
state bank said in a joint statement Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh Telegraph Agency reported that one of the most
important factors underlying the stability of the financial market
is that the market has unpegged its linkage with its Russian
counterpart and only seven percent of its international
settlements is done in Russian roubles.
</P>
<P>
Another important factor, as the statement said, is that the
gold and foreign exchange reserves in Kazakh state bank, which
total two billion U.S. dollars, well match its currency volume,
making it possible for its currency Tenge to remain stable.
</P>
<P>
A third factor, said the statement, is that Kazakhstan is quite
independent from its creditors, as the country's expenditures
related to its domestic and foreign debts account for only nine
percent of its national budget.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, to head off possible negative impact that the
ongoing economic crisis would incur, the Kazakh government and its
state bank have taken a series of measures aimed at consolidating
the country's financial system and maintaining a steady economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
To spur its domestic production, Kazakhstan has lowered its
transportation fees for mineral products, adjusted its tax rates
and cancelled its levying of double value-added taxes on goods
imported from members of the Commonwealth of Independent States.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, to ensure a stable Tenge, the state bank has
introduced a floating exchange rate system which sets the exchange
rate on the basis of its macroeconomic targets and the
international financial situation.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the state bank will continue its strict control
over banking liabilities and further improve its monitoring
mechanism to ensure the stability of the banking system.
</P>
<P>
The above measures, the statement said, have well protected the
Kazakh economy from being disturbed by external factors so that a
stable domestic financial market is guaranteed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980820.0251 </DOCNO>
