<HEADLINE> UNDP Launches 26 Mln Dollar Environment Grant in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) has launched an environment grant in Bangladesh
involving 26 million U.S. dollars, it was learned from the UNDP
representative office here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Letters of Agreement to this effect was signed here Wednesday
by the Environment and Forest Ministry's joint secretary Abdur
Rashid and heads of 20 agencies of government departments, and
other national and international organizations.
</P>
<P>
The grant will be used to implement a program described as
Sustainable Environment Management, according to the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The five-year program, which will unite the government and
other development agencies concerned in the country, will be
implemented by national director of the program and joint
secretary of the Ministry of Environment and Forest Abdur Rashid
and representatives of the signatory agencies.
</P>
<P>
The program is a follow-up action program for implementation of
the National Environment Management Action Plan.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of the program will help this South Asian
country strengthen government efforts in poverty alleviation
through adoption of environmental measures leading to sustainable
use of resources and management and for sustainable human
development. 
</P>
