<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, August 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST -- Hungarian Minister for Agriculture and Rural
Development Torgyan Jozsef announced Wednesday that his country
will stop selling land to foreigners.
</P>
<P>
He told a rally in the small southern city of Opusztaszer that
many foreigners wanted to buy a piece of land in Hungary on the
excuse of European integration.
</P>
<P>
He said that allowing foreigners to own Hungary's land was not
a necessary condition for the country to join the integration
process. (Hungary-Land Selling)
</P>
