<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern China Gets Country's Longest Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region will complete a 635-km-long expressway from
Guilin, the famous tourist city, to the industrial base of Liuzhou
and the port city of Beihai next year.
</P>
<P>
The Guilin-Beihai expressway was begun in 1993 and will be 300
km longer than the Shenyang-Dalian Expressway in Liaoning Province
and the Jinan-Qingdao Expressway in Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Huang Zhendong, the Minister of Communications, says that the
expressway will help both social and economic development in the
heavily-populated region.
</P>
<P>
Chu Zhitian, of the region's Communications Department, says
that the Guilin to Liuzhou and Nanning to Fangcheng sections have
been built and the rest will be completed next year.
</P>
<P>
It will cut the trip from Guilin to Beihai to 6 hours, and is
expected to increase the region's GDP by 4 billion yuan annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
