<HEADLINE> Hingis Advances at Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland advanced into the third round of the Canadian Open at
Austrian Sylvia Plischke's expense in Montreal on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Hingis routed Plischke 6-4, 6-1 in less than
one hour and faces the 16th seed Ai Sugiyama of Japan next round.
</P>
<P>
Hingis is aiming for her first title in three months in
Canada's second largest city of Montreal. She has won none since
the Italian Open event in May.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Wednesday, second seed and Wimbledon champion Jana
Novatna of the Czech Republic downed Russia's Elena Likhovtseva
7-5, 6-2, running her consecutive match victory streak to 17.
</P>
<P>
No. 3 seed Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain also advanced to
the next round, beating Karina Habsudova of Slovakia 0-6, 7-5,
6-2.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez is slated to meet France's Nathalie Tauziat, a 6-3,
6-3 winner over Kimberly Po of the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
