<HEADLINE> Mexican President to Attend Rio Group Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Congress
Wednesday approved an application by President Ernesto Zedillo to
attend the 12th summit of the Rio Group scheduled for Panama in
September.
</P>
<P>
The Rio Group, consisting of Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil,
Colombia, Chile, Ecuador, Mexico, Panama, Paraguay, Peru, Uruguay
and Venezuela, was set up in 1986 to promote the integration of
Latin America.
</P>
<P>
In his application, Zedillo described the summit as the most
representative regional political forum in Latin America .
</P>
<P>
Juan Antonio Garcia, senator of the National Action party,
urged Zedillo to call for firm steps to form a consolidate Latin
America at the summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
