<DOCNO> XIE19980820.0274 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Plans to Buy 1.2 Million Tons of Rice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government plans
to purchase 1.2 million tons of rice through international tenders
in August and September, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
"Indonesia will tender for 600,000 tons of rice on August 26
and another 600,000 tons in September. This is part of our plans
to import 3.1 million tons of rice in the 1998/99 fiscal year,"
State Minister for Food A.M. Saefuddin said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the government has already imported 1 million tons of
rice on a commercial basis in the financial year. It also signed
bilateral deals and received grants for an additional 1 million
tons, Antara News Agency Thursday quoted the minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
Officials said rice production has fallen due to last year's
prolonged drought and a decrease in land under rice cultivation.
Unhusked rice production is estimated to fall 6.25 percent to 46.3
million tons in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
