<HEADLINE> Stopping Smuggling In Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Tibet has stopped 9 cases of
smuggling in the first half of this year and seized 240 million
yuan worth of goods in the process.
</P>
<P>
The number of major smuggling cases in the region has dropped
75 percent from the same period last year, according to local
officials, and the smuggling of drugs has almost been eliminated
in the regional capital, Lhasa, which has given priority to combating
organized smuggling and has cracked down at the border, especially
where the population is sparse, and has successfully destroyed
several major smuggling groups.
</P>
<P>
Tibet is near to drug sources and has an increasingly large
migrant population and has had a rise in smuggling cases in the
past few years.  
