<HEADLINE> Contact Lens Inventor Dies in Prague </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Otto Wichterle, former president
of the Czech Academy of Sciences and inventor of the contact lens,
died in Prague on Tuesday. He was 84.
</P>
<P>
Born in 1913, Wichterle devoted his life to his country's
scientific development and registered more than 150 patents.
</P>
<P>
As a world-renowned polymer chemist, he invented the method
for synthesizing nylon fiber in the early 1940s.
</P>
<P>
His invention of the contact lens in 1960 made him famous
around the world.
</P>
<P>
In 1990, Wichterle was elected president of the Academy of
Sciences of Czechoslovakia. He remained on the post after Czech
independence in 1993. 
</P>
