<HEADLINE> Ogunkoya Upsets Fredericks in African Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAKAR, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's rising sprint star Seun
Ogunkoya upset the world and Olympic silver medallist Frankie
Fredericks of Namibia to win the African Championships 100 meters
title here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ogunkoya posted a personal best time of 9.94 seconds, with
pre-race favourite Fredericks timing 9.97 ahead of Ghana's Leo
Mills Myles in 10.10.
</P>
<P>
Former world champion Samuel Matete of Zambia won the 400
meters hurdles in 48.57 seconds, well clear of Zimbabwean Kenneth
Harden (49.39) and Senegal's Ibou Faye (49.49).
</P>
<P>
Mary Onyali won the women's 100m in 11.05 as Nigeria took all
three medals, Endurance Ojokolo second in 11.O8 and Rose Aboaja
in 11.31.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's Adere Brhane won the women's 5,OOOm in 15 minutes
54.3 seconds ahead of Kenyan Sally Barbosio and another
Ethiopian, Merima Demboba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
