<HEADLINE> Supreme People's Court Dismisses Chen Xitong's Appeal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- China's Supreme People's Court
dismissed here today the appeal by Chen Xitong, former secretary
of the Beijing Municipal Committee of the Communist Party of
China, and affirmed the original judgement.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court pronounced the decision to the public
this morning.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xitong was earlier sentenced to 16 years imprisonment on
charges of corruption and dereliction of duty by the Beijing
Municipal Higher People's Court. He disagreed with the verdict,
a judgement of first instance, and appealed to the Supreme
People's Court within the legal deadline.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal Higher People's Court sentenced on July
31 Chen Xitong to 13 years imprisonment on the charge of
corruption and to four years on the charge of dereliction of duty.
</P>
<P>
As a cumulative punishment for the two crimes, Chen shall serve
16 years in prison, the verdict said, and the bribes he accepted
shall be confiscated and turned over to the State Treasury.
</P>
</TEXT>
