<HEADLINE> Sir Bobby Charlton Highly Praises Cantona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Manchester United legend Sir
Bobby Charlton highly praised French soccer star Eric Cantona,
saying the club would never again see the like of the player.
</P>
<P>
The French star spent four and half years in the English
premiership club and brought a series success to the team, which
won four league titles, including two league and cup doubles.
</P>
<P>
After Cantona returned to Old Trafford, a year on from
quitting the game, to finally say his goodbyes in a match
organised to raise money for the Munich Memorial fund on Tuesday,
Sir Bobby gave his measured views on the maverick Frenchman.
</P>
<P>
"Eric Cantona was very special to this club and one wonders if
there will be another like him here," he said.
</P>
<P>
"He has a fantastic gift of tidying everything up. Before an
attack on goal he tidies everything up. He waits for every thing
to be in place before he releases the ball and it's a gift very
few people have.
</P>
<P>
"He's never afraid to be adventurous and never afraid to take
chances, and he very rarely got tackled because he has this
tremendous radar and a great awareness of what was going on
around him.
</P>
<P>
Sir Bobby was happy to put Cantona on a level with the many
great players to have graced Old Trafford, including himself.
</P>
<P>
"Without question he is up there with the Laws, Charltons and
Bests. At this club at the time he was here he was unsurpassed.
</P>
<P>
Current United manager Alex Ferguson, the man who signed
Cantona from Leeds for 1.2 million pounds (1.94 million U.S.
dollars)in 1992, believes the Frenchman was his best ever signing.
</P>
<P>
Ferguson points to the way Cantona was able to handle the
pressure of being the man the fans believed would take them to
the title.
</P>
<P>
"He's had the biggest affect a player has had in any of my
teams, and the greatest thing about him was that he came onto the
stage at Old Trafford as if he was born to play here," he
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
