<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Fourth-seeded Jonas Bjorkman
of Sweden was an upset victim Wednesday at the 745,000 U.S.
dollars RCA tennis championship in Indianapolis, the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The defending champion Bjorkman lost a 7-5, 6-3 match to Au
stralian Jason Stoltenberg.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman led the ATP Tour with 69 match wins and finished as
the world's fourth-ranked player last year, but has won only 22
of 41 matches this year.
</P>
<P>
French Open finalist Alex Corretja of Spain, the sixth
seed,advanced with a 6-3, 6-7 (7-2), 7-5 triumph over Austrlian
Scott Draper. But his countryman Albert Costa was beaten by
Australian David Wheaton 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Two other seeds were knocked off Wednesday as Ramon Delgado of
Paraguay ousted No. 9 Cedric Pioline 7-6 (7-3), 6-1, and Moroccan
Hicham Arazi eliminated 10th seed Felix Mantilla of Spain 6-2,
4-6,6-4.
</P>
<P>
Moving into the next round are Mark Philippoussis of
Australia, Francisco Clavet of Spain, Wayne Ferreira of South
Africa, and Byron Black of Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Marcelo Rios of Chile, who barely hung on to the No. 1 ranking
in the world last week, captured his first-ever win as the
top-ranked player in the world on Tuesday, dispatching American
Bob Bryan in a second round match.
</P>
<P>
Rios leads the ATP Tour with five titles this year, including
three Super 9 titles. He has compiled a 46-10 record and is the
top seed for this event.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Greg Rusedski of Britain and Fifth seed Andre
Agassi of the United States are seeking third-round berths in
Wednesday's matches. 
