<HEADLINE> Britain Sends More Troops to Brazzaville, Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The British government announced
Wednesday it would send more troops to Brazzaville, capital of the
Congo Republic, in case British nationals have to be evacuated
from the neighboring Democratic Republic of the Congo.
</P>
<P>
Last week, British Foreign Office advised British nationals to
leave the Democratic Republic of the Congo following a worsening
civil war in the country.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for British Ministry of Defense was quoted by
Reuters as saying early Wednesday it had sent 75 marine commandos
from Ascension Island to Brazzaville to join 45 British soldiers
who have been there since Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman stressed that the British government was "keeping
a close eye on the situation. There is obviously a possibility of
an evacuation being required."
</P>
<P>
Another 120 personnel would be sent from Britain to the
Gabonese capital Libreville to provide logistical support and
reinforcements, the spokesman added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
